The solve function calculates the sum by iterating from 1 to n (inclusive) and for each i, it checks if i is even or not. If i is even, it is added to the sum, otherwise, it is subtracted.

The main part of the code reads the number of test cases t from the input and for each test case, it reads the value of n and calls the solve function to calculate the sum. The result is printed on the standard output.

